<paragraph blockId="25.[189,1399,918,1124]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<keyLead pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
3. Telson distally truncated and slightly concave; ventral border of coxae 1-2 smooth; posterior border of basis of P5-7 with very weak crenulations; carpus of Gn1-2 equal to propodus.............................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName authority="(M. Sars, 1859)" baseAuthorityName="M. Sars" baseAuthorityYear="1859" box="[1021,1398,989,1016]" class="Malacostraca" family="Calliopiidae" genus="Halirages" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulvocinctus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1021,1207,989,1016]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">H. fulvocinctus</emphasis>
(M. 
<bibRefCitation author="Sars M." box="[1265,1390,989,1016]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="122 - 163" refId="ref14602" refString="Sars M. 1859. Oversigt over de i den norskarctiske region forekommende krebsdyr. Forhandlingar i Videnskabs-Selskabet i Kristiania 1858: 122 - 163." type="journal article" year="1859">Sars, 1859</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[189,1399,918,1124]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<keyLead pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
– Telson pointed, with large distal tooth flanked by 2 pairs of small lateral subdistal teeth; ventral border of coxae 1-2 and posterior border of basis of P5-7 distinctly serrate; carpus of Gn1-2 distinctly longer than propodus........................................................................................................ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="dAcoz" authorityYear="2012" box="[1156,1301,1097,1123]" class="Malacostraca" family="Calliopiidae" genus="Halirages" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stappersi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1156,1301,1097,1123]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">H. stappersi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1308,1399,1098,1124]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<paragraph blockId="25.[189,1399,1163,1369]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<keyLead pageId="25" pageNumber="26">4. Ventral lobe of head produced into a sharp tooth; carpus of Gn1-2 about 4 x as long as broad or narrower; at least some segments of pleon with posterodorsal tooth*; telson pointed; bathyal and abyssal species ..................................................................................................................................... 5</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[189,1399,1163,1369]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<keyLead pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
– Ventral lobe of head bluntly subquadrate; carpus of Gn1-2 a bit less than 2 x as long as broad; pleon smooth, segments without posterodorsal tooth; telson truncated; infralittoral species....................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Stephensen, 1931" authorityName="Stephensen" authorityYear="1931" box="[1065,1399,1342,1369]" class="Malacostraca" family="Calliopiidae" genus="Halirages" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mixtus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1065,1185,1342,1369]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">H. mixtus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Stephensen K." box="[1191,1399,1342,1368]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="179 - 290" refId="ref14854" refString="Stephensen K. 1931. Crustacea Malacostraca. VII. (Amphipoda. III). The Danish Ingolf-Expedition 3 (11): 179 - 290." type="journal article" year="1931">Stephensen, 1931</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<paragraph blockId="25.[189,1399,1408,1471]" box="[189,1399,1408,1435]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<keyLead box="[189,1399,1408,1435]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">5. Eyes present ......................................................................................................................................... 6</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[189,1399,1408,1471]" box="[196,1399,1444,1471]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<keyLead box="[196,1399,1444,1471]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">– Eyes absent........................................................................................................................................... 7</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<paragraph blockId="25.[189,1399,1510,1788]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<keyLead pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
6. Eye large and broad; coxa 1 with anteroventral corner pointing anteriorly; ventral border of coxa 1 with about 20 pronounced serrations; posteroventral corner of basis of P7 forming a sharp square angle; pereionite 7 (and often 6) and pleonites 1-2 with posterodorsal tooth; tip of telson tridentate ........................................................................................ 
<taxonomicName authority="G. O. Sars, 1877" authorityName="G. O. Sars" authorityYear="1877" box="[986,1399,1617,1644]" class="Malacostraca" family="Calliopiidae" genus="Halirages" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="qvadridentatus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[986,1202,1617,1644]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">H. qvadridentatus</emphasis>
G.O. 
<bibRefCitation author="Sars G. O." box="[1274,1399,1618,1644]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="237 - 271" refId="ref14490" refString="Sars G. O. 1877. Prodromus descriptionis crustaceorum et pycnogonidarum, qvae in expeditione Norvegica anno 1876, observavit. Archiv for Mathematik og Naturvidenskab 2: 337 - 271 [sic.] [= 237 - 271]." type="journal article" year="1877">Sars, 1877</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[189,1399,1510,1788]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<keyLead pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
– Eye small and subreniform; coxa 1 with anteroventral corner forming a square angle; ventral border of coxa 1 with about 10 weak crenulations; posteroventral corner of basis of P7 bluntly angular; pereionite 7 (but never 6) and pleonites 1-2 with posterodorsal tooth; tip of telson with a single distal tooth .......................................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authorityName="dAcoz" authorityYear="2012" box="[1183,1301,1761,1788]" class="Malacostraca" family="Calliopiidae" genus="Halirages" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cainae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1183,1301,1761,1788]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">H. cainae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1308,1399,1762,1788]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
