<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="25.[189,1399,1929,2027]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
* The pleon of the 
<typeStatus box="[427,478,1930,1956]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">type</typeStatus>
specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gurjanova" authorityYear="1946" box="[656,817,1929,1955]" class="Malacostraca" family="Calliopiidae" genus="Halirages" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gorbunovi">
<emphasis box="[656,817,1929,1955]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">H. gorbunovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(and only known specimens) is missing and its ornamentation is therefore unknown. However, since that species looks very similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="G. O. Sars" authorityYear="1877" box="[1182,1391,1965,1991]" class="Malacostraca" family="Calliopiidae" genus="Halirages" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="qvadridentatus">
<emphasis box="[1182,1391,1965,1991]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">H. qvadridentatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it is assumed that some of the posterior body segments have a posterodorsal tooth.
</paragraph>
